		<!-- Tutorial pages -->
		<Intro>Hi, sunshine! Sorting gems from The Never Mine is a really important job. Let me show you how to do it!</Intro>
		<Basics>Match three gems of the same color. The gems can be in a row or in a column.</Basics>
		<Match>Start by choosing a gem. Next choose a gem above, below, or next to it to make those 2 gems switch places.</Match>
		<Swap>The gems will switch places ONLY when the switch creates a 3-gem match. All three matching gems will disappear into the sorting bins!</Swap>
		<Fill>Each time you make a 3-gem match, new gems will take their place so that you can continue making more matches.</Fill>
		<MatchMore>Matching more than three gems gives you big bonuses!</MatchMore>
		<YouTry>Now you give it a try! Swap two gems to make a 3-gem match.</YouTry>
		<Needs>For the Easy and Medium levels, you can match any 3 gems. In higher levels, you'll have to match specific TYPES of gems for it to count. </Needs>
		<Timer>Oh, and watch the clock! Make all your matches fast and you'll get a bonus!</Timer>
		<ByeBye>I'll be right here with you, alright? Now let's get matching, sunshine!</ByeBye>
		<Impatient>Match 3 of the same kind of gem to clear them!</Impatient>

		<!-- Instructions -->
		<instruction0><![CDATA[Click on pairs of gems to switch their places. You can only switch gems when the switch makes three or more matching gems in a row or column.]]></instruction0>
		<instruction1><![CDATA[Match more than three gems to earn bonuses and power-ups!]]></instruction1>
		<instruction2><![CDATA[Complete the level goal within a certain amount of time for a bonus. Complete it before time runs out, or the game will end.]]></instruction2>
		<instruction3><![CDATA[If you ever get stuck, you'll have a few hints to help find matches.]]></instruction3>
		<instruction4><![CDATA[Most power-ups can be switched with other gems without making a match.]]></instruction4>
		<instruction5><![CDATA[Hazards can't be switched. Try using a power-up to get rid of them.]]></instruction5>
		
